6010/** \test BG box crash -- chunks are messed up. Observed for real. */
6011static int HTPBodyReassemblyTest01(void)
6012{
6013 int result = 0;
6014 HtpTxUserData htud;
6015 memset(&htud, 0x00, sizeof(htud));
6016 HtpState hstate;
6017 memset(&hstate, 0x00, sizeof(hstate));
6018 Flow flow;
6019 memset(&flow, 0x00, sizeof(flow));
6020 AppLayerParserState *parser = AppLayerParserStateAlloc();
6021 htp_tx_t tx;
6022 memset(&tx, 0, sizeof(tx));
6023
6024 hstate.f = &flow;
6025 flow.alparser = parser;
6026
6027 uint8_t chunk1[] = "--e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"uploadfile\"; filename=\"D2GUef.jpg\"\r";
6028 uint8_t chunk2[] = "POST /uri HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: hostname.com\r\nKeep-Alive: 115\r\nAccept-Charset: utf-8\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux i686; rv:9.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/9.0.1\r\nAccept: text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8\r\nConnection: keep-alive\r\nContent-length: 68102\r\nReferer: http://otherhost.com\r\nAccept-Encoding: gzip\r\nContent-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nCookie: blah\r\nAccept-Language: us\r\n\r\n--e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"uploadfile\"; filename=\"D2GUef.jpg\"\r";
6029
6030 int r = HtpBodyAppendChunk(NULL, &htud.request_body, chunk1, sizeof(chunk1)-1);
6031 BUG_ON(r != 0);
6032 r = HtpBodyAppendChunk(NULL, &htud.request_body, chunk2, sizeof(chunk2)-1);
6033 BUG_ON(r != 0);
6034
6035 const uint8_t *chunks_buffer = NULL;
6036 uint32_t chunks_buffer_len = 0;
6037
6038 HtpRequestBodyReassemble(&htud, &chunks_buffer, &chunks_buffer_len);
6039 if (chunks_buffer == NULL) {
6040 goto end;
6041 }
6042#ifdef PRINT
6043 printf("REASSCHUNK START: \n");
6044 PrintRawDataFp(stdout, chunks_buffer, chunks_buffer_len);
6045 printf("REASSCHUNK END: \n");
6046#endif
6047
6048 HtpRequestBodyHandleMultipart(&hstate, &htud, &tx, chunks_buffer, chunks_buffer_len);
6049
6050 if (htud.request_body.content_len_so_far != 669) {
6051 printf("htud.request_body.content_len_so_far %"PRIu64": ", htud.request_body.content_len_so_far);
6052 goto end;
6053 }
6054
6055 if (hstate.files_ts != NULL)
6056 goto end;
6057
6058 result = 1;
6059end:
6060 return result;
6061}

6063/** \test BG crash */
6064static int HTPSegvTest01(void)
6065{
6066 int result = 0;
6067 Flow *f = NULL;
6068 uint8_t httpbuf1[] = "POST /uri HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: hostname.com\r\nKeep-Alive: 115\r\nAccept-Charset: utf-8\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux i686; rv:9.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/9.0.1\r\nAccept: text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8\r\nConnection: keep-alive\r\nContent-length: 68102\r\nReferer: http://otherhost.com\r\nAccept-Encoding: gzip\r\nContent-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nCookie: blah\r\nAccept-Language: us\r\n\r\n--e5a320f21416a02493a0a6f561b1c494\r\nContent-Disposition: form-data; name=\"uploadfile\"; filename=\"D2GUef.jpg\"\r";
6069 uint32_t httplen1 = sizeof(httpbuf1) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
6070 char input[] = "\
6071%YAML 1.1\n\
6072---\n\
6073libhtp:\n\
6074\n\
6075 default-config:\n\
6076 personality: IDS\n\
6077 double-decode-path: no\n\
6078 double-decode-query: no\n\
6079 request-body-limit: 0\n\
6080 response-body-limit: 0\n\
6081";
6082
6083 ConfCreateContextBackup();
6084 ConfInit();
6085 HtpConfigCreateBackup();
6086 ConfYamlLoadString(input, strlen(input));
6087 HTPConfigure();
6088
6089 TcpSession ssn;
6090 HtpState *http_state = NULL;
6091 AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
6092
6093 memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
6094
6095 f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
6096 if (f == NULL)
6097 goto end;
6098 f->protoctx = &ssn;
6099 f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6100 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6101
6102 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6103
6104 SCLogDebug("\n>>>> processing chunk 1 <<<<\n");
6105 int r = AppLayerParserParse(
6106 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER | STREAM_START, httpbuf1, httplen1);
6107 if (r != 0) {
6108 printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
6109 goto end;
6110 }
6111 SCLogDebug("\n>>>> processing chunk 1 again <<<<\n");
6112 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, httpbuf1, httplen1);
6113 if (r != 0) {
6114 printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
6115 goto end;
6116 }
6117
6118 http_state = f->alstate;
6119 if (http_state == NULL) {
6120 printf("no http state: ");
6121 goto end;
6122 }
6123
6124 AppLayerDecoderEvents *decoder_events = AppLayerParserGetDecoderEvents(f->alparser);
6125 if (decoder_events != NULL) {
6126 printf("app events: ");
6127 goto end;
6128 }
6129 result = 1;
6130end:
6131 if (alp_tctx != NULL)
6132 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6133 HTPFreeConfig();
6134 ConfDeInit();
6135 ConfRestoreContextBackup();
6136 HtpConfigRestoreBackup();
6137 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6138 UTHFreeFlow(f);
6139 return result;
6140}

6142/** \test Test really long request, this should result in HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG */
6143static int HTPParserTest14(void)
6144{
6145 size_t len = 18887;
6146 TcpSession ssn;
6147 char input[] = "\
6148%YAML 1.1\n\
6149---\n\
6150libhtp:\n\
6151\n\
6152 default-config:\n\
6153 personality: IDS\n\
6154 double-decode-path: no\n\
6155 double-decode-query: no\n\
6156 request-body-limit: 0\n\
6157 response-body-limit: 0\n\
6158";
6159 AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
6160 FAIL_IF_NULL(alp_tctx);
6161
6162 memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
6163
6164 ConfCreateContextBackup();
6165 ConfInit();
6166 HtpConfigCreateBackup();
6167 ConfYamlLoadString(input, strlen(input));
6168 HTPConfigure();
6169
6170 char *httpbuf = SCMalloc(len);
6171 FAIL_IF_NULL(httpbuf);
6172 memset(httpbuf, 0x00, len);
6173
6174 /* create the request with a longer than 18k cookie */
6175 strlcpy(httpbuf, "GET /blah/ HTTP/1.1\r\n"
6176 "Host: myhost.lan\r\n"
6177 "Connection: keep-alive\r\n"
6178 "Accept: */*\r\n"
6179 "User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/29.0.1547.76 Safari/537.36\r\n"
6180 "Referer: http://blah.lan/\r\n"
6181 "Accept-Encoding: gzip,deflate,sdch\r\nAccept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.8\r\n"
6182 "Cookie: ", len);
6183 size_t o = strlen(httpbuf);
6184 for ( ; o < len - 4; o++) {
6185 httpbuf[o] = 'A';
6186 }
6187 httpbuf[len - 4] = '\r';
6188 httpbuf[len - 3] = '\n';
6189 httpbuf[len - 2] = '\r';
6190 httpbuf[len - 1] = '\n';
6191
6192 Flow *f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
6193 FAIL_IF_NULL(f);
6194 f->protoctx = &ssn;
6195 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6196 f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6197
6198 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6199
6200 uint32_t u;
6201 for (u = 0; u < len; u++) {
6202 uint8_t flags = 0;
6203
6204 if (u == 0) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START;
6205 else if (u == (len - 1)) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_EOF;
6206 else flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
6207
6208 (void)AppLayerParserParse(
6209 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, flags, (uint8_t *)&httpbuf[u], 1);
6210 }
6211 HtpState *htp_state = f->alstate;
6212 FAIL_IF_NULL(htp_state);
6213
6214 htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
6215 FAIL_IF_NULL(tx);
6216 FAIL_IF(tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET);
6217 FAIL_IF(tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1);
6218
6219 void *txtmp = AppLayerParserGetTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, f->alstate, 0);
6220 AppLayerDecoderEvents *decoder_events =
6221 AppLayerParserGetEventsByTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, txtmp);
6222 FAIL_IF_NULL(decoder_events);
6223
6224 FAIL_IF(decoder_events->events[0] != HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG);
6225
6226 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6227 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6228 UTHFreeFlow(f);
6229 SCFree(httpbuf);
6230 HTPFreeConfig();
6231 ConfDeInit();
6232 ConfRestoreContextBackup();
6233 HtpConfigRestoreBackup();
6234 PASS;
6235}

6237/** \test Test really long request (same as HTPParserTest14), now with config

6241 int result = 0;

6245 TcpSession ssn;

6247 int r = 0;

6249%YAML 1.1\n\
6250---\n\
6251libhtp:\n\
6252\n\
6253 default-config:\n\
6254 personality: IDS\n\
6255 double-decode-path: no\n\
6256 double-decode-query: no\n\
6257 request-body-limit: 0\n\
6258 response-body-limit: 0\n\
6259 meta-field-limit: 20000\n\
6260";
6261 AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
6262
6263 memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
6264
6265 ConfCreateContextBackup();
6266 ConfInit();
6267 HtpConfigCreateBackup();
6268 ConfYamlLoadString(input, strlen(input));
6269 HTPConfigure();
6270
6271 httpbuf = SCMalloc(len);
6272 if (unlikely(httpbuf == NULL))
6273 goto end;
6274 memset(httpbuf, 0x00, len);
6275
6276 /* create the request with a longer than 18k cookie */
6277 strlcpy(httpbuf, "GET /blah/ HTTP/1.1\r\n"
6278 "Host: myhost.lan\r\n"
6279 "Connection: keep-alive\r\n"
6280 "Accept: */*\r\n"
6281 "User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/29.0.1547.76 Safari/537.36\r\n"
6282 "Referer: http://blah.lan/\r\n"
6283 "Accept-Encoding: gzip,deflate,sdch\r\nAccept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.8\r\n"
6284 "Cookie: ", len);
6285 size_t o = strlen(httpbuf);
6286 for ( ; o < len - 4; o++) {
6287 httpbuf[o] = 'A';
6288 }
6289 httpbuf[len - 4] = '\r';
6290 httpbuf[len - 3] = '\n';
6291 httpbuf[len - 2] = '\r';
6292 httpbuf[len - 1] = '\n';
6293
6294 f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
6295 if (f == NULL)
6296 goto end;
6297 f->protoctx = &ssn;
6298 f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6299 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6300
6301 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6302
6303 uint32_t u;
6304 for (u = 0; u < len; u++) {
6305 uint8_t flags = 0;
6306
6307 if (u == 0) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START;
6308 else if (u == (len - 1)) flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_EOF;
6309 else flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
6310
6311 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, flags, (uint8_t *)&httpbuf[u], 1);
6312 if (r != 0) {
6313 printf("toserver chunk %" PRIu32 " returned %" PRId32 ", expected"
6314 " 0: ", u, r);
6315 goto end;
6316 }
6317 }
6318 htp_state = f->alstate;
6319 if (htp_state == NULL) {
6320 printf("no http state: ");
6321 goto end;
6322 }
6323
6324 htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
6325 if (tx == NULL || tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET || tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1)
6326 {
6327 printf("expected method M_GET and got %s: , expected protocol "
6328 "HTTP/1.1 and got %s \n", bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_method),
6329 bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_protocol));
6330 goto end;
6331 }
6332
6333 void *txtmp = AppLayerParserGetTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, f->alstate, 0);
6334 AppLayerDecoderEvents *decoder_events =
6335 AppLayerParserGetEventsByTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, txtmp);
6336 if (decoder_events != NULL) {
6337 printf("app events: ");
6338 goto end;
6339 }
6340
6341 result = 1;
6342end:
6343 if (alp_tctx != NULL)
6344 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6345 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6346 UTHFreeFlow(f);
6347 if (httpbuf != NULL)
6348 SCFree(httpbuf);
6349 HTPFreeConfig();
6350 ConfDeInit();
6351 ConfRestoreContextBackup();
6352 HtpConfigRestoreBackup();
6353 return result;
6354}

6356/** \test Test unusual delims in request line HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_REQUEST_FIELD_TOO_LONG */
6357static int HTPParserTest16(void)

6360 Flow *f = NULL;

6373 "Referer: http://blah.lan/\r\n"
6374 "Accept-Encoding: gzip,deflate,sdch\r\nAccept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.8\r\n"
6375 "Cookie: blah\r\n\r\n";
6376 size_t len = sizeof(httpbuf) - 1;
6377
6378 f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
6379 if (f == NULL)
6380 goto end;
6381 f->protoctx = &ssn;
6382 f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6383 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6384
6385 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6386
6387 uint8_t flags = STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_START|STREAM_EOF;
6388
6389 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, flags, (uint8_t *)httpbuf, len);
6390 if (r != 0) {
6391 printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
6392 goto end;
6393 }
6394
6395 htp_state = f->alstate;
6396 if (htp_state == NULL) {
6397 printf("no http state: ");
6398 goto end;
6399 }
6400
6401 htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(htp_state, 0);
6402 if (tx == NULL || tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET || tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1)
6403 {
6404 printf("expected method M_GET and got %s: , expected protocol "
6405 "HTTP/1.1 and got %s \n", tx ? bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_method) : "tx null",
6406 tx ? bstr_util_strdup_to_c(tx->request_protocol) : "tx null");
6407 goto end;
6408 }
6409
6410#ifndef FUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION
6411//these events are disabled during fuzzing as they are too noisy and consume much resource
6412 void *txtmp = AppLayerParserGetTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, f->alstate, 0);
6413 AppLayerDecoderEvents *decoder_events =
6414 AppLayerParserGetEventsByTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP1, txtmp);
6415 if (decoder_events == NULL) {
6416 printf("no app events: ");
6417 goto end;
6418 }
6419
6420 if (decoder_events->events[0] != HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_METHOD_DELIM_NON_COMPLIANT) {
6421 printf("HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_METHOD_DELIM_NON_COMPLIANT not set: ");
6422 goto end;
6423 }
6424
6425 if (decoder_events->events[1] != HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_URI_DELIM_NON_COMPLIANT) {
6426 printf("HTTP_DECODER_EVENT_URI_DELIM_NON_COMPLIANT not set: ");
6427 goto end;
6428 }
6429#endif
6430
6431 result = 1;
6432end:
6433 if (alp_tctx != NULL)
6434 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6435 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6436 UTHFreeFlow(f);
6437 return result;
6438}

6447 "LD-agent\r\nHost: 209.205.196.16\r\n\r\n";

6449 uint8_t httpbuf2[] = "NOTHTTP\r\nSOMEOTHERDATA";
6450 uint32_t httplen2 = sizeof(httpbuf2) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
6451 uint8_t httpbuf3[] = "STILLNOTHTTP\r\nSOMEMOREOTHERDATA";
6452 uint32_t httplen3 = sizeof(httpbuf3) - 1; /* minus the \0 */

6457

6459

6464 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6465

6470 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6471

6473 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT | STREAM_START, httpbuf2, httplen2);
6474 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6475

6477 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT | STREAM_START, httpbuf3, httplen3);
6478 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6479

6481 FAIL_IF_NULL(http_state);
6482 htp_tx_t *tx = HTPStateGetTx(http_state, 0);
6483 FAIL_IF_NULL(tx);

6485 FAIL_IF_NULL(h);
6486
6487 FAIL_IF(tx->request_method_number != HTP_M_GET);
6488 FAIL_IF(tx->request_protocol_number != HTP_PROTOCOL_1_1);
6489
6490 FAIL_IF(tx->response_status_number != 0);
6491 FAIL_IF(tx->response_protocol_number != -1);
6492
6493 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);

6496 PASS;

6720/** \test multi transactions and cleanup */
6721static int HTPParserTest25(void)
6722{
6723 AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
6724 FAIL_IF_NULL(alp_tctx);
6725
6726 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6727 TcpSession ssn;
6728 memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
6729
6730 Flow *f = UTHBuildFlow(AF_INET, "1.2.3.4", "1.2.3.5", 1024, 80);
6731 FAIL_IF_NULL(f);
6732 f->protoctx = &ssn;
6733 f->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6734 f->alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6735
6736 const char *str = "GET / HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: www.google.com\r\nUser-Agent: Suricata/1.0\r\n\r\n";
6737 int r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER | STREAM_START,
6738 (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6739 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6740 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6741 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6742 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6743 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6744 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6745 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6746 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6747 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6748 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6749 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6750 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6751 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6752 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6753 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6754 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6755 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6756 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6757 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6758 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6759 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6760 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6761
6762 str = "HTTP 1.1 200 OK\r\nServer: Suricata/1.0\r\nContent-Length: 8\r\n\r\nSuricata";
6763 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT | STREAM_START,
6764 (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6765 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6766 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6767 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6768 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6769 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6770 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6771 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6772 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6773 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6774 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6775 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6776 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6777 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6778 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6779 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6780 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6781 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6782 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6783 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6784 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6785 NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6786 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6787
6788 AppLayerParserTransactionsCleanup(f);
6789
6790 uint64_t ret[4];
6791 UTHAppLayerParserStateGetIds(f->alparser, &ret[0], &ret[1], &ret[2], &ret[3]);
6792 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[0] == 8); // inspect_id[0]
6793 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[1] == 8); // inspect_id[1]
6794 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[2] == 8); // log_id
6795 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[3] == 8); // min_id
6796
6797 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER | STREAM_EOF,
6798 (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6799 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6800 AppLayerParserTransactionsCleanup(f);
6801
6802 UTHAppLayerParserStateGetIds(f->alparser, &ret[0], &ret[1], &ret[2], &ret[3]);
6803 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[0] == 8); // inspect_id[0] not updated by ..Cleanup() until full tx is done
6804 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[1] == 8); // inspect_id[1]
6805 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[2] == 8); // log_id
6806 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[3] == 8); // min_id
6807
6808 r = AppLayerParserParse(NULL, alp_tctx, f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT | STREAM_EOF,
6809 (uint8_t *)str, strlen(str));
6810 FAIL_IF_NOT(r == 0);
6811 AppLayerParserTransactionsCleanup(f);
6812
6813 UTHAppLayerParserStateGetIds(f->alparser, &ret[0], &ret[1], &ret[2], &ret[3]);
6814 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[0] == 9); // inspect_id[0]
6815 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[1] == 9); // inspect_id[1]
6816 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[2] == 9); // log_id
6817 FAIL_IF_NOT(ret[3] == 9); // min_id
6818
6819 HtpState *http_state = f->alstate;
6820 FAIL_IF_NULL(http_state);
6821
6822 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6823 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6824 UTHFreeFlow(f);
6825
6826 PASS;
6827}

6829static int HTPParserTest26(void)
6830{
6831 char input[] = "\
6832%YAML 1.1\n\
6833---\n\
6834libhtp:\n\
6835\n\
6836 default-config:\n\
6837 personality: IDS\n\
6838 request-body-limit: 1\n\
6839 response-body-limit: 1\n\
6840";
6841 ConfCreateContextBackup();
6842 ConfInit();
6843 HtpConfigCreateBackup();
6844 ConfYamlLoadString(input, strlen(input));
6845 HTPConfigure();
6846
6847 Packet *p1 = NULL;
6848 Packet *p2 = NULL;
6849 ThreadVars th_v;
6850 DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = NULL;
6851 DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
6852 Flow f;
6853 uint8_t httpbuf1[] = "GET /alice.txt HTTP/1.1\r\n\r\n";
6854 uint32_t httplen1 = sizeof(httpbuf1) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
6855 uint8_t httpbuf2[] = "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n"
6856 "Content-Type: text/plain\r\n"
6857 "Content-Length: 228\r\n\r\n"
6858 "Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank."
6859 "Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank.";
6860 uint32_t httplen2 = sizeof(httpbuf2) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
6861 uint8_t httpbuf3[] = "Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank.\r\n\r\n";
6862 uint32_t httplen3 = sizeof(httpbuf3) - 1; /* minus the \0 */
6863 TcpSession ssn;
6864 HtpState *http_state = NULL;
6865 AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
6866 FAIL_IF_NULL(alp_tctx);
6867
6868 memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(th_v));
6869 memset(&f, 0, sizeof(f));
6870 memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
6871
6872 p1 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
6873 p2 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
6874
6875 FLOW_INITIALIZE(&f);
6876 f.protoctx = (void *)&ssn;
6877 f.proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
6878 f.flags |= FLOW_IPV4;
6879
6880 p1->flow = &f;
6881 p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
6882 p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
6883 p1->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
6884 p2->flow = &f;
6885 p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT;
6886 p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
6887 p2->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
6888 f.alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP1;
6889
6890 StreamTcpInitConfig(true);
6891
6892 de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
6893 FAIL_IF_NULL(de_ctx);
6894
6895 de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
6896
6897 de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert http any any -> any any "
6898 "(filestore; sid:1; rev:1;)");
6899 FAIL_IF_NULL(de_ctx->sig_list);
6900
6901 SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
6902 DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
6903
6904 int r = AppLayerParserParse(
6905 &th_v, alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOSERVER, httpbuf1, httplen1);
6906 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6907
6908 http_state = f.alstate;
6909 FAIL_IF_NULL(http_state);
6910
6911 /* do detect */
6912 SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
6913
6914 FAIL_IF((PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1)));
6915
6916 /* do detect */
6917 SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
6918
6919 FAIL_IF((PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1)));
6920
6921 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6922 &th_v, alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, httpbuf2, httplen2);
6923 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6924
6925 http_state = f.alstate;
6926 FAIL_IF_NULL(http_state);
6927
6928 /* do detect */
6929 SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p2);
6930
6931 FAIL_IF(!(PacketAlertCheck(p2, 1)));
6932
6933 r = AppLayerParserParse(
6934 &th_v, alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP1, STREAM_TOCLIENT, httpbuf3, httplen3);
6935 FAIL_IF(r != 0);
6936
6937 http_state = f.alstate;
6938 FAIL_IF_NULL(http_state);
6939
6940 FileContainer *ffc = HTPStateGetFiles(http_state, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
6941 FAIL_IF_NULL(ffc);
6942
6943 File *ptr = ffc->head;
6944 FAIL_IF(ptr->state != FILE_STATE_CLOSED);
6945
6946 AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
6947 DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
6948 DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
6949 StreamTcpFreeConfig(true);
6950
6951 HTPFreeConfig();
6952 FLOW_DESTROY(&f);
6953 UTHFreePackets(&p1, 1);
6954 UTHFreePackets(&p2, 1);
6955 ConfDeInit();
6956 ConfRestoreContextBackup();
6957 HtpConfigRestoreBackup();
6958 PASS;
6959}
6960
6961static int HTPParserTest27(void)
6962{
6963 HTPCfgDir cfg;
6964 memset(&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
6965 cfg.body_limit = 1500;
6966 FileReassemblyDepthEnable(2000);
6967
6968 uint32_t len = 1000;
6969
6970 HtpTxUserData *tx_ud = SCMalloc(sizeof(HtpTxUserData));
6971 FAIL_IF_NULL(tx_ud);
6972
6973 tx_ud->tsflags |= HTP_STREAM_DEPTH_SET;
6974 tx_ud->request_body.content_len_so_far = 2500;
6975
6976 FAIL_IF(AppLayerHtpCheckDepth(&cfg, &tx_ud->request_body, tx_ud->tsflags));
6977
6978 len = AppLayerHtpComputeChunkLength(tx_ud->request_body.content_len_so_far,
6979 0,
6980 FileReassemblyDepth(),
6981 tx_ud->tsflags,
6982 len);
6983 FAIL_IF(len != 1000);
6984
6985 SCFree(tx_ud);
6986
6987 PASS;
6988}
